2026-05-15 | Special Keyboard Maximum A’s

	Question
Return maximum possible A's after n operations.
	Key Insight
At some point:
		it becomes better to:
				Ctrl+A → Ctrl+C → multiple Ctrl+V
Instead of typing individual A's.
So for every position:
		try breaking at earlier point.
	Approach
1.	Define:
		dp[i] =
			max A's possible using i operations  
2.	Base case:
		dp[i] = i
		(by pressing A every time)
3.	For every i:
		try all breakpoints j:
				before:
					dp[j]
				then:
					Ctrl+A
					Ctrl+C
					pastes
4.	Formula:
		dp[i] = max(
				dp[j] * (i-j-1)
		)
Why?
After Ctrl+A and Ctrl+C:
		remaining operations are pastes.
	Time Complexity
	O(n²)
	Space Complexity
	O(n)
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    int optimalKeys(int n) {
        vector<int> dp(n + 1, 0);
        for(int i = 1; i <= n; i++){
            // press A directly
            dp[i] = i;
            for(int j = 1; j <= i - 3; j++){
                // Ctrl+A, Ctrl+C, then paste
                dp[i] = max(dp[i],
                            dp[j] * (i - j - 1));
            }
        }
        return dp[n];
    }
};
	Key Insight
The optimal strategy eventually becomes:
		build some text once
		then repeatedly paste it  
This is a classic:
		DP partition optimization problem.
